@startuml Component Diagram - Complete Architecture Overview (Simplified)
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml
title Complete Architecture: Thin Wrapper Pattern (Business Logic in Node.js)

Container_Boundary(renderer, "Renderer Process (Angular)") {

    ' ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ' ║  LAYER 1: PRESENTATION                                              ║
    ' ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
    Component(components_layer, "Layer 1: Components", "Smart Components", "UI rendering + user interaction\n(10 components)")

    ' ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ' ║  LAYER 2: STATE MANAGEMENT                                          ║
    ' ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
    Component(state_layer, "Layer 2: State", "RxJS BehaviorSubject", "Single source of truth\n(nav_state, import_state, search_state)")

    ' ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ' ║  LAYER 3: DOMAIN SERVICES (Thin Wrappers)                           ║
    ' ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
    Component(domain_layer, "Layer 3: Services", "Coordination Services", "Thin wrappers for IPC\n(Navigation, Import, Search,\nVerification, Export, Metadata)")

    ' ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ' ║  LAYER 4: INFRASTRUCTURE                                            ║
    ' ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
    Component(infrastructure_layer, "Layer 4: Infrastructure", "Support Services", "IPC Client, Error Handler,\nNotification, Query Validator,\nPerformance Monitor, Audit Logger")

    ' ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ' ║  LAYER 5: FRAMEWORK                                                 ║
    ' ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
    Component(bridge_layer, "Layer 5: Context Bridge", "Electron IPC", "Boundary: Renderer ↔ Main Process")
}

Container_Boundary(main, "Main Process (Node.js)") {
    Component(backend_layer, "Business Logic Layer", "Node.js Services", "WHERE WORK HAPPENS:\n• Search algorithms\n• Indexing & database\n• Verification logic\n• File I/O\n• AI embeddings")
}

' Layer interactions
Rel(components_layer, state_layer, "Subscribe to")
Rel(state_layer, domain_layer, "Updated by")
Rel(domain_layer, infrastructure_layer, "Use")
Rel(infrastructure_layer, bridge_layer, "Use")
Rel(bridge_layer, backend_layer, "IPC messages")

' Return flow
Rel(backend_layer, bridge_layer, "Return results")
Rel(bridge_layer, infrastructure_layer, "Deliver results")
Rel(infrastructure_layer, domain_layer, "Return data")
Rel(domain_layer, state_layer, "Update state")
Rel(state_layer, components_layer, "Notify subscribers")

note as architecture
  **SIMPLIFIED ARCHITECTURE: Thin Wrapper Pattern**
  
  Key Principle:
  All algorithmic/business logic → Node.js backend
  Angular → UI rendering + IPC coordination only
  
  Angular Responsibility:
  ✓ User interface (components)
  ✓ Local state (RxJS observables)
  ✓ IPC coordination (services)
  ✓ Error handling & notifications
  ✓ Audit logging coordination
  
  Node.js Responsibility:
  ✓ Search algorithms (text, semantic)
  ✓ Indexing & database operations
  ✓ Verification logic
  ✓ File I/O & buffering
  ✓ AI embeddings
  ✓ Data persistence
  
  Benefits:
  • Reduced Angular bundle size
  • Easier to maintain (clear boundaries)
  • Scalable (add algorithms in Node.js)
  • Testable (mock IPC Client)
  • No duplicate logic
end note

@enduml
